Autonomous Hardware Resource Orchestrator
Overview
This framework provides an autonomous, hardware-aware PowerShell orchestration engine. It is designed to maximize computational efficiency by dynamically probing the host environment and scaling task execution based on available resources.

Core Capabilities
Autonomous Resource Probing: The system continuously monitors the hardware landscape to identify high-performance compute providers.

Intelligent Prioritization: Built-in logic identifies and "favorites" preferred hardware (such as CUDA-enabled devices) to minimize latency.

Resilient Fallback: When primary high-performance hardware is unavailable, the orchestrator automatically cascades to the next most efficient available compute node.

Networked Scalability: The architecture is designed to handle hardware distribution, allowing for seamless scaling across networked compute resources.

Logic Implementation
The orchestrator operates via an event-driven loop that evaluates the system state to ensure optimal resource allocation:

PowerShell
# Example: Autonomous Probe and Orchestration
function Get-PrioritizedComputeTarget {
    # Probes host environment for accelerated compute providers
    $Device = Identify-BestHardware -Criteria "Performance"
    
    if ($Device.IsAccelerated) {
        return $Device.Path # Prioritized path
    } else {
        return "STANDARD_COMPUTE_NODE" # Fallback path
    }
}
Security & IP Integrity
To ensure intellectual property remains secure, this framework utilizes Environment Abstraction:

No Hardcoded Paths: The engine uses dynamic variable resolution rather than static file paths.

Decoupled Architecture: The resource-selection logic is separated from the execution payload.

Zero-Drift Posture: The system is designed to maintain a consistent state, regardless of the underlying host environment.

